{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7fe08c60-ae56-4e0c-9e21-d7733210fccb","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (.NET 6.0+ required) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (.NET 6.0+ required) |\n\nTwo of your three target frameworks (`net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`) are no longer supported. You'd need to update them to at least `net6.0` (or ideally `net8.0`/`net9.0`).\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n- MSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package.\n- Some APIs were removed or changed (e.g., `Assert.That` removals, class/method cleanup attributes behavior changes).\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update the csproj roughly to:\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"62e8908e-ce0c-4bb9-9f8a-02a612d28bc8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. The user wants to migrate to MSTest v3. Let me think about compatibility issues:\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ for .NET (Core) targets, and .NET Framework 4.6.2+ for .NET Framework targets.\n- Actually, let me be more precise. MSTest v3 dropped support for:\n  - .NET 5.0 (which is out of support)\n  - .NET Core 3.1 (which is out of support)\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2 is still supported (minimum supported .NET Framework version)\n\nSo the user will face compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` since MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later for .NET Core targets, while `net462` should remain compatible.\n\nMSTest v3 also consolidates into a single `MSTest` package instead of separate framework and adapter packages, along with some API changes and removals that could affect existing test code.","outputTokens":706,"requestId":"042D:C23BC:5CD18E:6D8F09:69E831B5"},"id":"f93a0523-26a1-4c69-ab43-6759f60ff12d","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:26:14.745Z","parentId":"a81df242-9ea8-48ce-9479-4981a43814d6"}
